<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Defs>
    <!--
        RELIGION CATEGORY MEME SORTING DEFS
        =====================================
        
        These defs categorize vanilla memes as Religion, Ideology, or Both.
        This controls which memes appear in the Religion vs Ideology wizard steps.
        
        Category values:
            - "Religion"  = meme only appears in religion system
            - "Ideology"  = meme only appears in ideology system
            - "Both"      = meme appears in both systems
        
        Default (no entry): "Ideology"
        
        Structure memes define the worldview foundation (e.g., Structure_Animist, Structure_Ideological).
        Normal memes add specific beliefs (e.g., Transhumanist, Proselytizer).
        Both types are categorized here.
        
        
        HOW TO MAKE A PATCH (for mod authors)
        ======================================
        
        If your mod adds custom memes and you want them to work with Ideology & Religion Rework,
        create an XML file in your mod's Defs/ directory with entries like this:
        
        <Defs>
            <IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryMemeDef>
                <defName>CatMeme_YourMemeName</defName>
                <targetDefName>YourMemeDefName</targetDefName>
                <category>Religion</category>
            </IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryMemeDef>
        </Defs>
        
        The defName must be unique across all mods.
        The targetDefName must match your MemeDef's defName exactly.
        The category determines where your meme appears in the wizard:
            "Religion" = Step 1 (Religion memes)
            "Ideology" = Step 3 (Ideology memes)
            "Both"     = appears in both steps
        
        To modify an existing entry, use XML patching:
        
        <Defs>
            <IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryMemeDef Name="CatMeme_Proselytizer">
                <category>Both</category>
            </IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryMemeDef>
        </Defs>
    -->

